summary: The UK Parliament is the main law-making body for the UK, Crown Dependencies, and British Overseas Territories. It's made up of the King, the House of Lords, and the House of Commons. The House of Commons is elected, with 650 members, and the government ministers are usually from this house. The House of Lords is the upper house, with appointed and hereditary members, and it can only delay laws. Parliament is very powerful and is one of the oldest in the world, often called the "mother of parliaments" due to its influence on other countries' political systems.
title: Parliament of the United Kingdom
